explanation: The final else branch did nothing (it contained only 'None'), so numbers in the range 10^8 to 10^9-1 were not handled. According to the specification we must truncate the hundred-thousands digit and all digits below it (i.e., set the last 6 digits to zero). I replaced the single incorrect line with a print that outputs N // 1000000 * 1000000 to perform that truncation.
